# template.env -- documents every secret/setting the deployed app depends on.
#
# Copy this to a gitignored `.env`, fill in real values, then run `make deploy`
# (or `./set-secrets.sh`) to push them to fly as *staged* secrets that the next
# deploy picks up -- so you never run `fly secrets set` by hand.
#
# Only collaboration mode (the fly deployment) needs any of this; plain local
# `uv run app.py` ignores it all. See DEPLOY.md for the full walkthrough.
#
# Two things are deliberately NOT plain KEY=VALUE lines here:
#
#   - The allowlist + repo wiring live in `/data/collab.json` on the fly volume
#     (so you can edit who's an editor/viewer without redeploying). Its presence
#     is also what turns collaboration mode ON. See collab.example.json.
#
#   - The SSH deploy key is multi-line, which `fly secrets import` can't parse,
#     so set-secrets.sh sends it separately from a gitignored `deploy_key` file
#     (mint it per DEPLOY.md step 3). The app writes it onto the volume and uses
#     it to clone/push the courses repo.

# --- Required secrets -------------------------------------------------------

# Signs the login session cookie. Generate ONCE and keep it stable -- changing
# it logs everyone out:
#   python3 -c 'import secrets; print(secrets.token_hex(32))'
FLASK_SECRET_KEY=<random 64-hex-char string>

# The GitHub OAuth app's client secret (GitHub -> Settings -> Developer settings
# -> OAuth Apps -> your app -> "Generate a new client secret"). DEPLOY.md step 2.
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=<GitHub OAuth client secret>

# --- Optional: env overrides for the non-secret collab.json settings --------
# These are NOT secret and normally live in /data/collab.json, but collab.py
# layers env on top of the file, so you can set them here instead if you'd
# rather keep everything in one place. Uncomment to use.

# The GitHub OAuth app's client ID (collab.json key: github_oauth.client_id).
#GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=<GitHub OAuth client ID>

# The courses repo the app clones and pushes to (collab.json key: repo).
#LESSON_COURSES_REPO=git@github.com:YOUR-USER/lesson-courses.git

# Dev only: enable the no-OAuth "sign in as anyone" button. NEVER set in prod.
#LESSON_DEV_LOGIN=1
